thread.title: Pa. Girls: Shanahan scores twice, and EA downs GA
thread.title_full: Pa. Girls: Shanahan scores twice, and EA downs GA

title: Pa. Girls: Shanahan scores twice, and EA downs GA
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports FRIENDS SCHOOLS LEAGUE
Moorestown Friends 2, George School 0: Micaela Coll and Alexis Kasper scored in the second half for the hosts. 
NONLEAGUE 
Christian Academy 4, Ridley 3, OT: Grace Cryan scored six minutes into extra time to complete her hat trick. Grace Gormley also scored. 
Upper Moreland 2, Merion Mercy 1: Brianna Byard and Phoebe Longstreth scored second- half goals for the hosts. 
Gwynedd Mercy 4, Wissahickon 1: Rachel Koller scored two goals, and Erica DeCandido and Shea Tomlinson also scored for the home squad. 
PUBLIC LEAGUE 
Central 6, Philadelphia Academy Charter 1: Djavon Dupree scored her second hat trick of the season. Amber Dilks made nine saves at home. 
Masterman 3, Science Leadership Academy 0: Vanessa Debekow, Maya Kilcullen, and Erin Roache scored for the visitors. FIELD HOCKEY 
FRIENDS SCHOOLS LEAGUE 
Friends' Central 3, Germantown Friends 2, OT: Anne Pizzini redirected a shot from Alyssa Holt at the top of the circle to give the visitors the victory. Cornell-bound keeper Maddie Henry made 23 saves. 
Friends Select 3, George School 1: Lizzie Augustine, Dom Dombici, and Millie Elsey scored goals at home. 
INTER-AC LEAGUE 
Episcopal Academy 4, Germantown Academy 3: Maddie Bacskai, Colby Gallagher, Margaux Paolino, and Corrine Zanolli scored second-half goals, and the hosts rallied from a two-goal deficit at the half. 
SUBURBAN ONE AMERICAN 
Wissahickon 4, Upper Dublin 1: Jessica Waite's hat trick led the way for the visitors. Sam Scoma also scored. Claire Tarzia made 10 saves. TENNIS 
PUBLIC LEAGUE AAA TOURNAMENT 
Central's Gabby Garrett won the singles championship at Lincoln. Tiffany Atmadja and Eryn Nguyen, also of Central, were doubles champions.
